CONTEXT
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The LLM has been:
1. Saying "I have created the task" without emitting <<ACTION>>...<<END>>.
2. Saying "Here are your tasks" without listing them.
3. Going silent (empty response) when chat history contains
   previous turns that confused it.
4. Hallucinating approvals with no worklog ID specified.

These are all prompt-discipline failures. The new prompts must:
- FORCE <<ACTION>> emission as the ONLY way to perform actions.
- FORCE rendering of snapshot data when user asks to view.
- FORCE explicit "missing parameter X" responses when params lack.
- FORBID confirmation messages without prior action emission.

